<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Ssh on memoria digital</title><link>https://volteret4.github.io/notas/tags/ssh/</link><description>Recent content in Ssh on memoria digital</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>es-es</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 31 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://volteret4.github.io/notas/tags/ssh/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Demasiados Intentos De Conexi√≥n Ssh</title><link>https://volteret4.github.io/notas/p/demasiados-intentos-de-conexi%C3%B3n-ssh/</link><pubDate>Thu, 31 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://volteret4.github.io/notas/p/demasiados-intentos-de-conexi%C3%B3n-ssh/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a class="link" href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/59429697/ssh-too-many-authentication-failures-error-when-trying-to-connect-to-raspberry" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>source&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The &lt;code>known_host&lt;/code> file isn&amp;rsquo;t related to your problem.&lt;br>
It&amp;rsquo;s seems to be the problem, that your agent knows too many keys.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You can try it with&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">ssh -o &lt;span class="nv">IdentityAgent&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>none -i private_key_file_for_raspberry ...
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>You can add this to your config file, too.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">4
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">5
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">HOST raspi42
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> hostname raspberry.myhome
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> user pi
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> IdentityAgent none
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> IdentityFile private_key_file_for_raspberry
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div></description></item><item><title>Eliminar Clave De Known_hosts</title><link>https://volteret4.github.io/notas/p/eliminar-clave-de-known_hosts/</link><pubDate>Thu, 24 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://volteret4.github.io/notas/p/eliminar-clave-de-known_hosts/</guid><description>&lt;p>Para eliminar las claves que referencien a dietpi:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> ssh-keygen -f &lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;/home/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nv">$USER&lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">/.ssh/known_hosts&amp;#34;&lt;/span> -R &lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;dietpi&amp;#34;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div></description></item><item><title>Sudo Pw Timeout</title><link>https://volteret4.github.io/notas/p/sudo-pw-timeout/</link><pubDate>Wed, 09 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://volteret4.github.io/notas/p/sudo-pw-timeout/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="-1-configurar-el-tiempo-antes-de-volver-a-pedir-la-contrase√±a">‚úÖ 1. &lt;strong>Configurar el tiempo antes de volver a pedir la contrase√±a&lt;/strong>
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Esto lo controla &lt;strong>sudo&lt;/strong> mediante la opci√≥n &lt;strong>timestamp_timeout&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="-c√≥mo-cambiarlo">üîß ¬øC√≥mo cambiarlo?
&lt;/h3>&lt;p>Edita o crea un archivo en &lt;code>/etc/sudoers.d/&lt;/code>, por ejemplo:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo visudo -f /etc/sudoers.d/timeout
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Y agrega esta l√≠nea:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">Defaults &lt;span class="nv">timestamp_timeout&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>&lt;span class="m">5&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>üïê Esto significa que &lt;strong>sudo recordar√° la contrase√±a durante 5 minutos&lt;/strong>. Puedes poner:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>&lt;code>0&lt;/code>: pide siempre la contrase√±a.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>&lt;code>-1&lt;/code>: no la vuelve a pedir durante la sesi√≥n.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;hr>
&lt;h2 id="-2-hacer-que-sudo-se">‚úÖ 2. &lt;strong>Hacer que sudo se &amp;ldquo;olvide&amp;rdquo; cuando cerr√°s SSH&lt;/strong>
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Esto se puede hacer de varias formas. La m√°s directa:&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="-m√©todo-usar-pam_exec-para-limpiar-sudo-al-cerrar-sesi√≥n">üîß M√©todo: usar &lt;code>pam_exec&lt;/code> para limpiar sudo al cerrar sesi√≥n
&lt;/h3>&lt;p>Edita el archivo PAM de tu shell, por ejemplo para &lt;code>bash&lt;/code> (esto depende de tu distribuci√≥n):&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo nano /etc/pam.d/sshd&lt;span class="sb">`&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Agrega esta l√≠nea al &lt;strong>final&lt;/strong> del archivo:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">session optional pam_exec.so &lt;span class="nv">type&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>close_session /usr/bin/sudo -K
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Esto ejecutar√° &lt;code>sudo -K&lt;/code> cuando se cierre una sesi√≥n SSH, que &lt;strong>borra el timestamp de sudo&lt;/strong>.&lt;/p>
&lt;hr>
&lt;h2 id="-alternativa-simple-alias-en-bash_logout">üß™ Alternativa simple: alias en &lt;code>.bash_logout&lt;/code>
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Si no quieres meterte con &lt;code>pam&lt;/code>, puedes hacer algo m√°s simple:&lt;/p>
&lt;p>En tu Raspberry o servidor remoto, edita:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">nano ~/.bash_logout
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Agreg√° esta l√≠nea:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo -K
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Eso hace que, cuando cierras una sesi√≥n interactiva (&lt;code>exit&lt;/code>, cerrar shell), se borre el cach√© de &lt;code>sudo&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>üìå Esto &lt;strong>no funciona&lt;/strong> si usas otro shell que no lee &lt;code>.bash_logout&lt;/code>, como &lt;code>zsh&lt;/code>. Para &lt;code>zsh&lt;/code>, puedes usar &lt;code>~/.zlogout&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;hr>
&lt;h2 id="-verificaci√≥n-r√°pida">üß† Verificaci√≥n r√°pida
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Pod√©s comprobar si el cach√© est√° activo con:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo -v
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Y ver si est√° activo con:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo -n &lt;span class="nb">true&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nb">echo&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;Tiene cach√© sudo&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">||&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nb">echo&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;No tiene cach√© sudo&amp;#34;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div></description></item></channel></rss>